The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	New Delhi, Sept. 20 (PTI): The Centre has directed states to be more proactive in probing crimes against women and file chargesheets within three months.          
	Terming the states performance in tackling such crimes disappointing, the home ministry has sent an advisory asking them to target pimps, brothel owners and clients instead of sex workers, who are the victims in most cases.                  
	Chennai (PTI): A 10-year-old boy allegedly set himself on fire after being chided by his teacher for not writing Tamil properly, police said on Sunday. Antony Pratheesh, a Class V student in a government school, was allegedly scolded and threatened with demotion to Class IV. He died in hospital.                  
	Coimbatore (PTI): An ice-cream container filled with gunpowder was found in front of an industrialists house here. A team from the bomb detection squad found that the container was filled with gunpowder, used in crackers, and took it for testing. There was no fuse to trigger an explosion.                   
	Manali (PTI): Himachal Pradesh police have stepped up security at Chabad House here, frequented by Israeli tourists, after Israeli security agencies warned its nationals of a very serious terror threat during the Jewish festive season. About 40,000 Israeli tourists visit the hill station every year.                  
	Jammu (PTI): An army jawan allegedly committed suicide by consuming poison at Kaluchak in Jammu district. Sepoy Divender Singh had just come back after 15 days leave and brought his wife and mother with him.                   
	 Chandigarh (PTI): Nearly half of Delhis landlords have not completed police verification of their tenants, statistics show. Of the 1,35,120 tenants traced by police till September 15 this year, 49 per cent were found to be staying in rented accommodation without mandatory verification.                                                                                                                           
